Benchmark pass done with real OS injection benchmarks.

Method used:

- Windows low-level mouse hook (WH_MOUSE_LL) counting injected WM_LBUTTONDOWN events.
- Click loops were run directly from each implementation.
- cpsDrops, jitter, and onlyInMinecraft were disabled for clean timing tests.
- 3 runs each per scenario.

Real click results (averages)

| Scenario | Java | Rust |
|---|---:|---:|
| Target 25 CPS (5s run) | 23.316 CPS | 25.067 CPS |
| Mean interval @25 | 42.889 ms | 39.990 ms |
| Interval jitter stdev @25 | 4.678 ms | 0.224 ms |
| P95 interval @25 | 49.360 ms | 40.104 ms |
| Target 100 CPS (3s run) | 94.968 CPS | 25.333 CPS (clamped to 25) |

Who's better by category (with latest rerun data)

- Accuracy to configured 25 CPS: Rust
- Timing consistency / smoother intervals: Rust
- Tail latency stability (p95/p99) at 25 CPS: Rust
- Maximum raw click throughput: Java
- Safety/guardrails (prevents unrealistic configs): Rust
